Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Halve and peel the @red onion{2}. Quarter each half. Pop the potatoes and onions on a large #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and sprinkle over the @dried thyme{1%tsp}. Toss to coat, then roast them on the top shelf of your oven until the potatoes are golden and the onions nice and soft, ~{25-35%minutes}, turn halfway.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Put the garlic in a #bowl{} with the @tomato puree{30%g}, @mango chutney{40%g} and 1 tbsp of water per person. Mix together and leave to the side.

Finely chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(finely chopped) (stalks and all) and pop in a #medium bowl{} with the @olive oil{for coating}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix together. Add the @skin-on British chicken breasts{2} to the bowl and turn to coat in the mixture.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium high heat (no oil). Once the pan is hot, lay in the chicken breasts skin side down and fry until the skin is golden, ~{4-5%minutes}. Turn and cook for ~{2%minutes} on the other side, then transfer to a #baking tray{} (skin side up) and pop on the middle shelf of your oven to roast until cooked, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the potatoes and onion are cooked, add the tomato/chutney mixture and mix together until they are nicely coated. Lay the @chopped kale{100%g} on top, drizzle with a little @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Return it to your oven and bake until the kale is crispy, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove the chicken from your oven and pop on a #board{} to rest for a couple of minutes. Mix the potatoes, onions and kale together in the tray and spoon onto plates. Thinly slice the chicken and serve on top. Enjoy!